<p>Straight to the point with this one. Let's say the date today is 16-06-2015 and the device date matches this. I'm trying to read it in this format, 16062015. However, the date is being shown to be one month behind i.e. 16052015. My code:</p>  <pre><code>public String getDate() {     Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();     int day = cal.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH);     int month = cal.get(Calendar.MONTH);     int year = cal.get(Calendar.YEAR);     String dayString = String.valueOf(day);     String monthString = String.valueOf(month);     String yearString = String.valueOf(year);     String date = dayString + "0" + monthString + yearString;     return date; } </code></pre>  <p>What could be the issue?</p>  <p>This is in J2ME. Device: Nokia 206.</p>